cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with broadcasting real-time flows in multi-hop wireless networks, which is a networking problem. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper considers the utility of packets delivered on time, which can be related to information theory. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a distributed protocol and algorithms for maximizing system utility, which falls under the category of distributed computing. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with optimizing the performance of a system, which can be related to systems and control. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - Although not the primary focus, the paper mentions simulation results, which may involve machine learning techniques.
